Google java format is not configurable by design ([have a look at this][1]) so there is no way for configuring a custom max line width. What you can do is to configure spotless plugin to work with a custom eclipse jdt formatter. [Here][2] you can see how this is done in the spotless documentation.

For example, for *gradle* you would have:
```
spotless {
  java {
    eclipse().configFile(&#39;custom-config.xml&#39;)
  }
}
```
Instead of:
```
spotless {
  java {
    googleJavaFormat()
  }
}
```


